SIMPLE: rheumatic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rheumatic
<hw>Rheu*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/
subject to a discharge or flux: cf. L. <ets>rheumaticus</ets>, F.
<ets>rhumatique</ets>. See <er>Rheum</er>, <er>Rheumatism</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Derived from, or having the character of, rheum;
rheumic.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to rheumatism;
<as>as, <ex>rheumatic</ex> pains or affections</as>; affected with
rheumatism; <as>as, a <ex>rheumatic</ex> old man</as>; causing
rheumatism; <as>as, a <ex>rheumatic</ex> day</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>rheumatic</qex> diseases do abound.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rheumatic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rheumatic
<hw>Rheu*mat"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One affected with
rheumatism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rheumatism</ent>⟦br⟧
